I"5<p>Barnet Council’s <a href="https://engage.barnet.gov.uk/1726/documents/1850">Draft Housing Strategy</a> describes the Granville Road estate as follows: <em>‘The quality of the estate is generally poor and it includes large areas of under-utilised and unstructured land.’</em></p>

<p>Barnet’s <a href="https://www.barnet.gov.uk/sites/default/files/assets/citizenportal/documents/planningconservationandbuildingcontrol/PlanningPolicy/LocalPlan/DPD/LocalPlanCoreStrategyDPDSeptember2012.pdf">Core Strategy</a> lists the Granville Road estate as one of its <em>‘failed housing estates’</em>, which <em>‘will be subject to long term programmes of regeneration in order to tackle poor quality housing, social isolation and transform these areas into successful mixed tenure places.’</em> (policy 7.2.12)</p>
